aa(lp167
VThis is a picture at Punta Tombo in February
p168
aVshowing all the penguins along the beach.
p169
aVI went there because the Japanese wanted to start harvesting them
p170
aVand turning them into high fashion golf gloves,
p171
aVprotein and oil.
p172
aVFortunately, nobody has harvested any penguins
p173
aVand we're getting over 100,000 tourists a year to see them.
p174
aVBut the population is declining
p175
aVand it's declined fairly substantially, about 21 percent
p176
aVsince 1987, when I started these surveys,
p177
aVin terms of number of active nests.
p178
aVHere, you can see where Punta Tombo is,
p179
aVand they breed in incredibly dense colonies.
p180
aVWe know this because of long-term science,
p181
aVbecause we have long-term studies there.
p182
aVAnd science is important in informing decision makers,
p183
aVand also in changing how we do
p184
aVand knowing the direction of change that we're going in.
